</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="W. Horn, 1934" authorityName="W. Horn" authorityYear="1934" box="[298,766,1036,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudominimum">
<emphasis box="[298,610,1036,1060]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Pogonostoma pseudominimum</emphasis>
W. 
<bibRefCitation author="Horn, W." box="[650,766,1037,1061]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" pagination="7 - 31" refId="ref5494" refString="Horn, W. (1934) Catalogue Bibliographique et synonymique des Cicindelides de Madagascar. In: Horn, W. &amp; Olsoufieff, G., Les Cicindelides de Madagascar (premiere partie). Memories de l'Academie Malgache, 20, 7 - 31 + 3 pls." type="journal article" year="1934">Horn, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(by original designation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1106,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,507,1106,1132]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Revised differential diagnosis</emphasis>
. Because of their extremely small to small, 
<quantity box="[1022,1160,1106,1133]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.45" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="5.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" unit="mm" value="6.45" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="5.4">5.4–7.5 mm</quantity>
long, black bodies, and 4–setose labrum, the four known species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[810,982,1143,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[810,982,1143,1168]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may resemble some species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeannel, 1946" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[224,566,1179,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microstenocera">
<emphasis box="[224,400,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Microstenocera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel, R." box="[408,566,1179,1205]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" refId="ref5545" refString="Jeannel, R. (1946) Coleopteres Carabiques de la region Malgache (premiere partie). Faune de l'empire francais. VI. Libraire Larosse, Paris, 372 pp." type="book" year="1946">Jeannel, 1946</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in contrast to the irregular elytral setal vesture in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[1253,1429,1179,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microstenocera">
<emphasis box="[1253,1429,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Microstenocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[315,487,1215,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[315,487,1215,1240]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by their regular elytral setal vesture, consisting of ornamental se- tae, which are confined to punctures—each ornamental seta (microtrichia) arising from anterior margin of corre- sponding puncture (as in the nominotypical subgenus, which, however, houses species with much larger body with multisetose labrum). Elytra shiny black, notably coarsely punctate throughout, with smooth, glabrous intervals. Pronotal disc sculptured by coarse, or very coarse, transverse-wavy, or partly anastomosing ridges. Head temples moderately long, approximately 2 times shorter than eyes. Galea entirely black (or with slightly brownish apex of terminal galeomere). Labial palpi black, or partly or entirely testaceous. Antennae entirely black, or black-brown, or (in one species) predominantly ivory-testaceous. Legs with apical half of mesofemora, or also metafemora, more or less conspicuously subclavate-dilated, entirely black, except for one species with markedly bicoloured femora and tibiae. Aedeagus of various shapes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1106,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,441,1574,1601]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Nomenclatorial note</emphasis>
. Because of their regular elytral setal vesture, species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1218,1390,1575,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[1218,1390,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been treated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Olsoufieff, G." box="[333,533,1611,1637]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" pagination="31 - 73" refId="ref6697" refString="Olsoufieff, G. (1934) Essai de Revision systematique et Biologie des Cicindelides de Madagascar. In: Horn, W. &amp; Olsoufieff, G., Les Cicindelides de Madagascar (deuxieme partie). Memoires de l'Academie Malgache, 20, pp. 31 - 73." type="journal article" year="1934">Olsoufieff (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel, R." box="[546,713,1611,1638]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" refId="ref5545" refString="Jeannel, R. (1946) Coleopteres Carabiques de la region Malgache (premiere partie). Faune de l'empire francais. VI. Libraire Larosse, Paris, 372 pp." type="book" year="1946">Jeannel (1946)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Horn, W." box="[771,911,1611,1637]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" pagination="7 - 31" refId="ref5494" refString="Horn, W. (1934) Catalogue Bibliographique et synonymique des Cicindelides de Madagascar. In: Horn, W. &amp; Olsoufieff, G., Les Cicindelides de Madagascar (premiere partie). Memories de l'Academie Malgache, 20, 7 - 31 + 3 pls." type="journal article" year="1934">Horn (1934)</bibRefCitation>
in the nominotypical subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1835" box="[1275,1429,1611,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1275,1429,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. When 
<bibRefCitation author="Rivalier, E." box="[225,397,1647,1673]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" pagination="269 - 338" refId="ref6843" refString="Rivalier, E. (1970) Le genre Pogonostoma (Col. Cicindelidae). Revision avec description d'especes nouvelles. Annales de la Societe entomologique de Franc e, New Series, 6, 269 - 338." type="journal article" year="1970">Rivalier (1970)</bibRefCitation>
established the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[688,860,1647,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[688,860,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the three above-mentioned species, he included also 
<taxonomicName authority="W. Horn, 1934" authorityName="W. Horn" authorityYear="1934" box="[204,645,1683,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiator">
<emphasis box="[204,470,1683,1709]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Pogonostoma gladiator</emphasis>
W. 
<bibRefCitation author="Horn, W." box="[517,645,1683,1709]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" pagination="7 - 31" refId="ref5494" refString="Horn, W. (1934) Catalogue Bibliographique et synonymique des Cicindelides de Madagascar. In: Horn, W. &amp; Olsoufieff, G., Les Cicindelides de Madagascar (premiere partie). Memories de l'Academie Malgache, 20, 7 - 31 + 3 pls." type="journal article" year="1934">Horn, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
there. Due to extremely distinctive diagnostic characters of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Pogonos- toma</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. Horn" authorityYear="1934" box="[213,519,1719,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiator" subGenus="Hornogeniatum">
(
<emphasis box="[222,399,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Hornogeniatum</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[415,519,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">gladiator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(unique within the whole genus), the species was placed later (
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J." box="[1214,1379,1719,1745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" refId="ref5728" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
) into a separate, monobasic subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Moravec, 2007" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" box="[516,874,1755,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Hornogeniatum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[516,693,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Hornogeniatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J." box="[700,874,1755,1781]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" refId="ref5728" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1106,2034]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,348,1790,1816]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[368,503,1791,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-29@7.[218,1369,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11–14. Distribution of Pogonostoma (Microgeniatum) in Madagascar. 11—P. (M.) pseudominimum W. Horn; 12— P. (M.) infimum Rivalier; 13—P. (M.) flavopalpale Jeannel; 14—P. (M.) signifemorale sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5778849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5778849/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Figs 11–14</figureCitation>
). Species of the subgenus are very rare, absent in most collections (including BMNH—see 
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J. &amp; Gillett, P. D. T." box="[307,581,1827,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" pagination="131 - 154" refId="ref6003" refString="Moravec, J. &amp; Gillett, P. D. T. (2009) Annotated list of specimens of Madagascan Cicindelidae deposited in The Natural History Museum London. Folia Heyrovskyana, Series A, 16, 131 - 154." type="journal article" year="2009">Moravec &amp; Gillett 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Behaviour of adults is similar to most species of the silvicolous and strictly arboreal genus; developmental stages unknown. Somewhat more common is only 
<emphasis box="[1066,1083,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">P</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName box="[1106,1280,1863,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[1106,1280,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">pseudomini- mum</emphasis>
W. 
<bibRefCitation author="Horn, W." box="[250,379,1899,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" pagination="7 - 31" refId="ref5494" refString="Horn, W. (1934) Catalogue Bibliographique et synonymique des Cicindelides de Madagascar. In: Horn, W. &amp; Olsoufieff, G., Les Cicindelides de Madagascar (premiere partie). Memories de l'Academie Malgache, 20, 7 - 31 + 3 pls." type="journal article" year="1934">Horn, 1934</bibRefCitation>
(type species of the subgenus), which is known from eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1075,1213,1899,1925]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(Antongil Bay, dis- trict of Maroantsetra), penetrating through the forest of the Mananara Nord National Park (Province of 
<collectingRegion box="[1306,1429,1935,1962]" country="Madagascar" name="Toamasina" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">Toamasina</collectingRegion>
) to central area of Central Highlands, through Antsianaka near Lac Alaotra and the forest of Didy (both in the district of Ambatondrazaka) up to the forest of Analamazaotra-Perinet (type locality) east of Moramanga. The 
<typeStatus box="[1308,1406,2007,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="526">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCount lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="2" pageNumber="526" type="male">1 ♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount box="[186,228,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
, 
<typeStatus box="[242,345,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">lectotype</typeStatus>
not designated) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. Horn" authorityYear="1934" box="[560,979,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudominimum" subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[560,577,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[601,775,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[793,979,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">pseudominimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are deposited in SDEI; other specimens examined are in MNHN, CCJM, CJVB and JWCW (
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J." box="[753,920,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" refId="ref5728" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
and recent personal data). The following two species have not been confirmed recently. 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeannel, 1946" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[629,1160,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavopalpale" subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[629,646,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[669,841,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[858,998,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">flavopalpale</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel, R." box="[1005,1160,223,249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" refId="ref5545" refString="Jeannel, R. (1946) Coleopteres Carabiques de la region Malgache (premiere partie). Faune de l'empire francais. VI. Libraire Larosse, Paris, 372 pp." type="book" year="1946">Jeannel, 1946</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<specimenCount pageId="3" pageNumber="527" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[260,384,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
(MNHN), caught in the forest of Piton Saint-Louis, north of Tolagnaro (= Fort Dauphin), 121 years ago. Only the male 
<typeStatus box="[438,536,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">holotype</typeStatus>
(MNHN) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rivalier, 1970" authorityName="Rivalier" authorityYear="1970" box="[686,1173,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infimum" subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[686,703,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[726,898,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[915,1007,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">infimum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rivalier, E." box="[1014,1173,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" pagination="269 - 338" refId="ref6843" refString="Rivalier, E. (1970) Le genre Pogonostoma (Col. Cicindelidae). Revision avec description d'especes nouvelles. Annales de la Societe entomologique de Franc e, New Series, 6, 269 - 338." type="journal article" year="1970">Rivalier, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
exists; it was caught in the deciduous forest of Analamerana, 
<quantity box="[584,657,330,357]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" unit="km" value="50.0">50 km</quantity>
south-east of 
<collectingRegion box="[818,953,331,357]" country="Madagascar" name="Antsiranana" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">Antsiranana</collectingRegion>
(= Diego Suarez) in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1301,1436,331,357]" name="Madagascar" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(in 
<date box="[190,345,366,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" value="1959-01">January 1959</date>
). Finally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Moravec &amp; Trýzna, 2021" authorityName="Moravec &amp; Trýzna" authorityYear="2021" box="[458,843,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signifemorale" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Microgeniatum">
<emphasis box="[458,475,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[500,672,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">Microgeniatum</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[689,843,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">signifemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[851,943,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[851,936,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known only from the single male caught recently in the dense, dry deciduous forest of the Ankarafantsika National Park in northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1360,403,429]" name="Madagascar" pageId="3" pageNumber="527">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
